#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:0.4"
msgid "Cīvaravagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:0.5"
msgid "8. Upakkhaṭasikkhāpada"
msgstr "8. The training rule on what is set aside"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-np8.1, pts-vp-en2.53, ms1V_2015
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro puriso pajāpatiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "At that time a certain man said to his wife,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.3"
msgid "“ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarena acchādessāmī”ti."
msgstr "“I’ll give a robe to Venerable Upananda.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.4"
msgid "Assosi kho aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu tassa purisassa imaṃ vācaṃ bhāsamānassa."
msgstr "A monk who was an alms-collector heard that man making that statement."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.5"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "He then went to Upananda"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.6"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.7"
msgid "“mahāpuññosi tvaṃ, āvuso upananda."
msgstr "“Upananda, you have much merit."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.8"
msgid "Amukasmiṃ okāse aññataro puriso pajāpatiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "I’ve just heard a man telling his wife"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.9"
msgid "‘ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarena acchādessāmī’”ti."
msgstr "that he’ll give you a robe.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.10"
msgid "“Atthāvuso, maṃ so upaṭṭhāko”ti."
msgstr "“He’s my supporter.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_2016
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.11"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto yena so puriso tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Upananda then went to that man"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.12"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ purisaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.13"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira maṃ tvaṃ, āvuso, cīvarena acchādetukāmosī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true that you desire to give me a robe?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: meyya → mayya (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.14"
msgid "“Api meyya, evaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "“Indeed,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.15"
msgid "‘ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarena acchādessāmī’”ti."
msgstr "that’s just what I was thinking.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.16"
msgid "“Sace kho maṃ tvaṃ, āvuso, cīvarena acchādetukāmosi, evarūpena cīvarena acchādehi."
msgstr "“If that’s the case, give me such-and-such a robe."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.17"
msgid "Kyāhaṃ tena acchannopi karissāmi yāhaṃ na paribhuñjissāmī”ti."
msgstr "For what’s the point of giving a robe that I won’t use?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.18"
msgid "Atha kho so puriso ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "That man grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.19"
msgid "“mahicchā ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā asantuṭṭhā."
msgstr "“These Sakyan ascetics have great desires; they are not content."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.20"
msgid "Nayime sukarā cīvarena acchādetuṃ."
msgstr "It’s no easy matter to give them a robe."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.21"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma ayyo upanando mayā pubbe appavārito maṃ upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjissatī”ti."
msgstr "How can Venerable Upananda come to me and specify the kind of robe he wants without first being invited by me?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, pts-vp-en2.54, ms1V_2017
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.22"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa purisassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of that man,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.23"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.24"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.25"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto pubbe appavārito gahapatikaṃ upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjissatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda approach a lay person and specify the kind of robe he wants without first being invited?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, pts-vp-pli3.216, ms1V_2018
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.26"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master …"

#. VAR: gahapatikaṃ → gahapatiṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.27"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, pubbe appavārito gahapatikaṃ upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you acted like this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.28"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.29"
msgid "“Ñātako te, upananda, aññātako”ti?"
msgstr "“Is he a relative of yours?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.30"
msgid "“Aññātako, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“No, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.31"
msgid "“Aññātako, moghapurisa, aññātakassa na jānāti patirūpaṃ vā appatirūpaṃ vā santaṃ vā asantaṃ vā."
msgstr "“Foolish man, people who are not related don’t know what’s appropriate and what’s inappropriate in dealing with each other, what’s right and what’s wrong."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.32"
msgid "Tattha nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, pubbe appavārito aññātakaṃ gahapatikaṃ upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjissasi."
msgstr "And still you went to an unrelated lay person and specified the kind of robe you wanted without first being invited."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.33"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.34"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.34a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: cīvaracetāpannaṃ → cīvara­ce­tāpanaṃ (s1-3, pts1)
#. REF: sc5, ms1V_2019
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.35"
msgid "“Bhikkhuṃ paneva uddissa aññātakassa gahapatissa vā gahapatāniyā vā cīvaracetāpannaṃ upakkhaṭaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "‘If a layman or laywoman has set aside a robe fund for an unrelated monk, thinking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.36"
msgid "‘iminā cīvaracetāpannena cīvaraṃ cetāpetvā itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ cīvarena acchādessāmī’ti;"
msgstr "‘With this robe fund I will buy a robe and give it to monk so-and-so;’"

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.55
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.37"
msgid "tatra ce so bhikkhu pubbe appavārito upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjeyya—"
msgstr "and if that monk, without first being invited, approaches them and specifies the kind of robe he wants, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.38"
msgid "‘sādhu vata maṃ āyasmā iminā cīvaracetāpannena evarūpaṃ vā evarūpaṃ vā cīvaraṃ cetāpetvā acchādehī’ti,"
msgstr "‘It would be good if you would use this robe fund to buy such-and-such a robe and then give it to me,’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:1.39"
msgid "kalyāṇakamyataṃ upādāya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "and he does so because he wants something nice, he commits and offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, pts-cs-bu-np8.2.1, ms1V_2020
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.1"
msgid "Bhikkhuṃ paneva uddissāti"
msgstr "For a […] monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.2"
msgid "bhikkhussatthāya, bhikkhuṃ ārammaṇaṃ karitvā, bhikkhuṃ acchādetukāmo."
msgstr "for the benefit of a monk; making a monk the object of consideration, one desires to give to him."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_2021
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.3"
msgid "Aññātako nāma"
msgstr "Unrelated:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.4"
msgid "mātito vā pitito vā yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā asambaddho."
msgstr "anyone who is not a descendant of one’s male ancestors going back seven generations, either on the mother’s side or on the father’s side."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms1V_2022
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.5"
msgid "Gahapati nāma"
msgstr "A layman:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.6"
msgid "yo koci agāraṃ ajjhāvasati."
msgstr "any man who lives in a house."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms1V_2023
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.7"
msgid "Gahapatānī nāma"
msgstr "A laywoman:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.8"
msgid "yā kāci agāraṃ ajjhāvasati."
msgstr "any woman who lives in a house."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_2024
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.9"
msgid "Cīvaracetāpannaṃ nāma"
msgstr "A robe fund:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.10"
msgid "hiraññaṃ vā suvaṇṇaṃ vā muttā vā maṇi vā pavāḷo vā phaliko vā paṭako vā suttaṃ vā kappāso vā."
msgstr "money, gold, a pearl, a gem, a coral, a crystal, cloth, thread, or cotton wool."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_2025
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.11"
msgid "Iminā cīvaracetāpannenāti"
msgstr "With this robe fund:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.12"
msgid "paccupaṭṭhitena."
msgstr "with that which is at one’s disposal."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_2026
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.13"
msgid "Cetāpetvāti"
msgstr "I will buy:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.14"
msgid "parivattetvā."
msgstr "having exchanged."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_2027
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.15"
msgid "Acchādessāmīti"
msgstr "I will […] give:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.16"
msgid "dassāmi."
msgstr "I will donate."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_2028
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.17"
msgid "Tatra ce so bhikkhūti"
msgstr "If that monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.18"
msgid "yaṃ bhikkhuṃ uddissa cīvaracetāpannaṃ upakkhaṭaṃ hoti so bhikkhu."
msgstr "the monk for whom the robe fund has been set aside."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc15, ms1V_2029
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.19"
msgid "Pubbe appavāritoti"
msgstr "Without first being invited:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.20"
msgid "pubbe avutto hoti—"
msgstr "he or she has not said beforehand:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.21"
msgid "“kīdisena te, bhante, cīvarena attho,"
msgstr "“Venerable, what kind of robe do you need?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.22"
msgid "kīdisaṃ te cīvaraṃ cetāpemī”ti?"
msgstr "What kind of robe can I buy for you?”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc16, ms1V_2030
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.23"
msgid "Upasaṅkamitvāti"
msgstr "Approaches him:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.24"
msgid "gharaṃ gantvā yattha katthaci upasaṅkamitvā."
msgstr "having gone to his house or having gone wherever."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc17, ms1V_2031
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.25"
msgid "Cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjeyyāti"
msgstr "Specifies the kind of robe he wants:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
#. REF: pts-vp-en2.56
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.26"
msgid "āyataṃ vā hotu vitthataṃ vā appitaṃ vā saṇhaṃ vā."
msgstr "please make it long or wide or closely woven or soft."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc18, pts-vp-pli3.217, ms1V_2032
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.27"
msgid "Iminā cīvaracetāpannenāti"
msgstr "This robe fund:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.28"
msgid "paccupaṭṭhitena."
msgstr "that which is at one’s disposal."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc19, ms1V_2033
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.29"
msgid "Evarūpaṃ vā evarūpaṃ vāti."
msgstr "Such-and-such:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.30"
msgid "Āyataṃ vā vitthataṃ vā appitaṃ vā saṇhaṃ vā."
msgstr "long or wide or closely woven or soft."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc20, ms1V_2034
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.31"
msgid "Cetāpetvāti"
msgstr "To buy:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.32"
msgid "parivattetvā."
msgstr "having exchanged."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc21, ms1V_2035
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.33"
msgid "Acchādehīti"
msgstr "Give:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.34"
msgid "dajjehi."
msgstr "donate."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc22, ms1V_2036
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.35"
msgid "Kalyāṇakamyataṃ upādāyāti"
msgstr "Because he wants something nice:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: sādhatthiko → sādhutthiko (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.36"
msgid "sādhatthiko mahagghatthiko."
msgstr "wanting something nice, wanting something expensive."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.37"
msgid "Tassa vacanena āyataṃ vā vitthataṃ vā appitaṃ vā saṇhaṃ vā cetāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr "If that lay person buys a robe that is long, wide, closely woven, or soft because of the monk’s statement, then for the act of making the statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.38"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the robe, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.39"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.40"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. HTML: <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.41"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in [Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17](pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13), with appropriate substitutions. "

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.42"
msgid "“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ pubbe appavārito aññātakaṃ gahapatikaṃ upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpannaṃ nissaggiyaṃ,"
msgstr "‘Venerables, this robe which I received after approaching an unrelated lay person and specifying the kind of robe I wanted without first being invited is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.43"
msgid "imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.44"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.45"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.1.46"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe back to you.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc23, pts-cs-bu-np8.2.2, ms1V_2037
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.2.1"
msgid "Aññātake aññātakasaññī pubbe appavārito gahapatikaṃ upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjati, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If the lay person is unrelated and the monk perceives them as unrelated, and, without first being invited, he approaches them and specifies the kind of robe he wants, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.2.2"
msgid "Aññātake vematiko pubbe appavārito gahapatikaṃ upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjati, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If the lay person is unrelated, but the monk is unsure if they are, and, without first being invited, he approaches them and specifies the kind of robe he wants, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.2.3"
msgid "Aññātake ñātakasaññī pubbe appavārito gahapatikaṃ upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjati, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If the lay person is unrelated, but the monk perceives them as related, and, without first being invited, he approaches them and specifies the kind of robe he wants, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24, ms1V_2038
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.2.4"
msgid "Ñātake aññātakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the lay person is related, but the monk perceives them as unrelated, he commit an offense of wrong conduct."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.57
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.2.5"
msgid "Ñātake vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the lay person is related, but the monk is unsure if they are, he commit an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.2.6"
msgid "Ñātake ñātakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If the lay person is related and the monk perceives them as related, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc25, pts-cs-bu-np8.2.3, ms1V_2039
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.3.2"
msgid "ñātakānaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is from relatives;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.3.3"
msgid "pavāritānaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is from those who have given an invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.3.4"
msgid "aññassatthāya,"
msgstr "if it is for the benefit of another;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.3.5"
msgid "attano dhanena,"
msgstr "if it is by means of his own property;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.3.6"
msgid "mahagghaṃ cetāpetukāmassa appagghaṃ cetāpeti,"
msgstr "if the lay person wishes to buy something expensive, but the monk gets them to buy something inexpensive;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.3.7"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.3.8"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc26, ms1V_2040
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:2.3.9"
msgid "Upakkhaṭasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The eighth rule, the training rule on what is set aside, is finished."
